# Red Team Tactics & Offensive Security Learning Path

Welcome to the **Red Team Tactics & Offensive Security Learning Path** repository. This project serves as a comprehensive structural framework, syllabus, and lab documentation hub for mastering adversarial simulations, vulnerability research, and structured offensive engagements. 

The curriculum maps core offensive concepts directly to the **MITRE ATT&CK® Framework** and translates theoretical research into reproducible, isolated lab environments.

---

## 📑 Core Syllabus Modules

### 1. Advanced Reconnaissance and OSINT
*   **Passive Reconnaissance:** Gathering intelligence without direct target interaction (DNS enumeration, WHOIS parsing, metadata extraction). Locating exposed infrastructure via internet-wide scanners like Shodan.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1595.002 - Active Scanning](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1595/002/)
*   **Active Reconnaissance:** Stealth port scanning, service enumeration, and OS fingerprinting using targeted scripting engines (e.g., Nmap Scripting Engine).
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1046 - Network Service Scanning](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1046/)
*   **OSINT Frameworks:** Utilizing Maltego and Recon-ng to build automated data-collection workflows, such as harvesting corporate structures and mapping employee profiles to corporate email syntax patterns.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1593 - Search Open Websites/Domains](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1593/)

### 2. Initial Access Techniques
*   **Phishing & Spear-Phishing:** Crafting highly targeted communication scenarios and setting up reverse-proxy infrastructure to capture credentials or deploy obfuscated payloads.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1566.001 - Spearphishing Attachment](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1566/001/)
*   **Credential Access:** Executing password spraying and pass-the-hash attacks while managing account lockout thresholds.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1110 - Brute Force](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1110/)
*   **Exploitation of Exposed Services:** Identifying and targeting misconfigured or unpatched edge devices, legacy services (RDP, SMB), or public applications.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing Application](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1190/)

### 3. Exploitation and Vulnerability Research
*   **Exploit Development:** Understanding low-level execution mechanics, memory corruption fundamentals (buffer overflows), and modern system mitigations like ASLR/DEP.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1068 - Exploitation for Privilege Escalation](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1068/)
*   **Web Application Exploitation:** Identifying and safely exploiting flaws within OWASP Top 10 categories, including SQL Injection (SQLi), Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), and CSRF.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1190 - Exploit Public-Facing Application](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1190/)
*   **Privilege Escalation:** Assessing local system security postures to elevate context from low-privilege users to root/SYSTEM via kernel exploits or configuration flaws (e.g., SUID binaries).

### 4. Lateral Movement and Persistence
*   **Pivoting & Internal Movement:** Navigating internal network segments using authentication tokens, Pass-the-Ticket strategies, and Living off the Land Binaries (LOLBins) like PsExec.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1021 - Remote Services](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1021/)
*   **Persistence Mechanisms:** Establishing durable access across reboots and configuration changes using scheduled tasks, registry modifications, or custom local backdoors.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1547 - Boot or Logon Autostart Execution](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1547/)

### 5. Evasion Techniques
*   **AV/EDR Bypassing:** Utilizing payload encoding, dynamic obfuscation, and encryption routines to minimize static and heuristic signatures.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1027 - Obfuscated Files or Information](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1027/)
*   **Network Evasion:** Routing Command and Control (C2) communications through encrypted proxies, multi-hop networks, or legitimate domain fronting paths.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1090 - Proxy](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1090/)
*   **Behavioral Evasion:** Blending malicious activities into standard OS processes using process hollowing or process masquerading techniques.
    *   *MITRE ATT&CK:* [T1036 - Masquerading](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1036/)

